<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_axxos" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>axxos</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>anxos</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>вина</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>guilt</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>причина</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>cause</q></cit></sense></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>axxos kænyn</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>обвинять</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>blame (v.)</q></cit></sense></re><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_axxos." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>ænæ axxosæj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>без вины</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>without fault</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>49</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>m’axxos næ wyd</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>не моя была вина</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>it was not my fault</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>122</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>anxos in æj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>(болезнь) его — от действия злой силы</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>his diseased is caused by the evil force</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"/><biblScope>27</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>næ ǧæwagi — anxosgænæg</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>в нужде ты (Уаскерги) нам помогаешь</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>you (Waskergi) help us in need</q></cit><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><bibl><ref target="#src_Gurdž._Wadž."/><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>ænæ axxosæj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>без вины</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>without fault</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>49</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>m’axxos næ wyd</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>не моя была вина</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>it was not my fault</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>122</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>anxos in æj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>(болезнь) его — от действия злой силы</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>his diseased is caused by the evil force</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"/><biblScope>27</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>næ ǧæwagi — anxosgænæg</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>в нужде ты (Уаскерги) нам помогаешь</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>you (Waskergi) help us in need</q></cit><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><bibl><ref target="#src_Gurdž._Wadž."/><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Может быть, из %iа%i + %iæm%i + %ikos%i, где %ikos%i — ‘работа’ (см. <xr><ref target="#entry_kūsyn"/></xr> | %ikosun%i). Семантика не препятствует такому разъяснению; ‘вина’ рассматривается как активное действие, как ‘работа’ („его вина“ = „его работа“), ср. <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/><w>laźä</w><gloss><q>работа</q></gloss></mentioned> → ‘вина’ (→ д. <xr><ref target="#entry_lazæ"/></xr> ‘вина’). По огласовке иронская форма с %iо%i (вместо ожидаемого %iū%i) должна рассматриваться как „дигоризм“; ср. <xr><ref target="#entry_æxx0ys"/></xr> | %iænxus%i ‘помощь’ из %i*æm-kus%i.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Perhaps, from %iа%i + %iæm%i + %ikos%i, where %ikos%i is ‘work’ (cf. <xr><ref target="#entry_kūsyn"/></xr> | %ikosun%i). The semantics does not preclude such clarification; ‘guilt’ is seen as an active action, as ‘work’ (“his guilt” = “his work”), cf. <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/><w>laźä</w><gloss><q>работа</q></gloss></mentioned> → ‘guilt’ (→ Digor <xr><ref target="#entry_lazæ"/></xr> ‘guilt’). Considering the vocalism, the Iron form %iо%i (instead of expected %iū%i) must be regarded as a “Digorism”; cf. <xr><ref target="#entry_æxx0ys"/></xr> | %iænxus%i ‘help’ from %i*æm-kus%i.</etym></entry>